This is our first Java project...
We are building a todo app using the tutorials on youtube
Here are the libraries we have added uptill now in our project
    1. Spring Web
    2. Spring Data JPA
    3. MySQL Driver
    4. Lombok
    5. Thymeleaf

Created a database first - todoApp and configured it into application.properties file

Created the following files
    1. Repository package - TaskRepo interface
    2. Modal Package - containing the overall task structure
    3. Controller Package - that will take values fro service layer and display them
    4. Service layer - that will take values from repository layer and provide it to controller layer

Created the function getAllTasks() to get all the task. We mapped it with the HTML tasks page
inside templates folder.

Completed the basic structure of thymeleaf that shows task

Completed the logic of adding data inside the database and display it...

Completed the logic of deleting the task and tto change the status of task to completed..

Added bootstrap to create the frontend...

Summary of this project
    1. Front-End is done through Thymeleaf and Bootstrap
    2. Backend is handled by SpringBoot Framework
